{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","level":2},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-611-Metal-for-VR","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-601-Introducing-Metal-2"]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-603-VR-with-Metal-2","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/603\/"}},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"VR with Metal 2","roleHeading":"WWDC17"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-603-vr-with-metal-2"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Metal 2 provides powerful and specialized support for Virtual Reality (VR) rendering and external GPUs. Get details about adopting these emerging technologies within your Metal 2-based apps and games on macOS High Sierra. Walk through integrating Metal 2 with the SteamVR SDK and learn about efficiently rendering to a VR headset. Understand how external GPUs take macOS graphics to a whole new level and see how to prepare your apps to take advantage of their full potential.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-601-Introducing-Metal-2":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-601-introducing-metal-2","title":"Introducing Metal 2","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-601-Introducing-Metal-2","abstract":[{"text":"Metal 2 provides near-direct access to the graphics processor (GPU), enabling your apps and games to realize their full graphics and compute potential. Dive into the breakthrough features of Metal 2 that empower the GPU to take control over key aspects of the rendering pipeline. Check out how Metal 2 enables essential tasks to be specified on-the-fly by the GPU, opening up new efficiencies for advanced rendering.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17","title":"WWDC17","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"kind":"article","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","type":"card"}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","title":"Learn More…"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-611-Metal-for-VR":{"abstract":[{"text":"On macOS, Metal 2 adds specialized support for virtual reality (VR) rendering and external GPUs. Learn about new features and optimizations to take advantage of these technologies within your Metal 2-based apps and games. Understand best practices for scheduling workloads across multiple GPUs and techniques for frame pacing while multi-threading.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-611-metal-for-vr","title":"Metal for VR","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-611-Metal-for-VR"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg"}],"type":"image","alt":null},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/603/":{"url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/603\/","checksum":null,"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/603\/"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image","alt":null}}}